HEADWORD: Trolley car
<hw>Trol"ley car</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A motor car powered by
electricity drawn from a trolley, and thus constrained to follow the
trolley lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><col><b>Trolley line</b></col>, <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>A trolley
<sd>(f)</sd>.</cd> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>The path along which a trolley car
runs.</cd>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trolley wire</ent>⟦br⟧
